cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.DM. 

The paper deals with online optimization of non-convex functions, which is a common problem in machine learning and optimization, hence cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely category. The paper also deals with algorithm selection problems for combinatorial settings, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of combinatorial algorithms and the focus on computational efficiency suggests cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as another likely category. The paper also deals with clustering problems, which falls under cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
